For Women’s Month in August, The Playhouse Company presents its famed South African Women’s Arts Festival (SAWAF).  Marking the Playhouse Company’s 21st Festival, the event is themed phenomenal woman to commemorate South African women in all aspects of life. Under the helm of critically acclaimed choreographer, David Gouldie, the Playhouse Company presents a brand new dance work, Handbag – Don’t clutch me too tight. The production is based on the real-life tales of the ladies who live at The Association For The Aged (TAFTA).